SIMPLE: fain
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fain
<hw>Fain</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>fain</ets>,
<ets>fagen</ets>, AS. <ets>f⟦ae⟧gen</ets>; akin to OS. <ets>fagan</ets>,
Icel. <ets>faginn</ets> glad; AS. <ets>f⟦ae⟧gnian</ets> to rejoice, OS.
<ets>fagan⟦omac⟧n</ets>, Icel. <ets>fagna</ets>, Goth.
<ets>fagin⟦omac⟧n</ets>, cf. Goth. <ets>fah⟦emac⟧ds</ets> joy; and fr.
the same root as E. <ets>fair</ets>. Srr <er>Fair</er>, <pos>a.</pos>,
and cf. <er>Fawn</er> to court favor.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Well-pleased; glad; apt; wont; fond; inclined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men and birds are <qex>fain</qex> of climbing high.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To a busy man, temptation is <qex>fain</qex>to climb up together
with his business.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Satisfied; contented; also, constrained.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The learned Castalio was <qex>fain</qex> to make trechers at Basle
to keep himself from starving.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fain
<hw>Fain</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With joy; gladly; -- with
<xex>wold</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He would <qex>fain</qex> have filled his belly with the husks that
the swine did eat.</q> <rj><qau>Luke xv. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Fain</qex> Would I woo her, yet I dare not.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fain
<hw>Fain</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To be glad ; to wish or
desire.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whoso fair thing does <qex>fain</qex> to see.</q>
<rj><qau>Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Faineancy</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Faineance</ent>⟦br⟧
